caption: Small park with a memorial on one end. The park itself is gated. It didn't have as much grassy area as the park across the road. The memorial is surrounded by a fence and there are seats around it. It was an interesting looking memorial with the leafy design.
Relatively large, gated area where dogs can run around freely.

Great dog park, busy one , many English speaking owners. Only I feel bad when kids comes at evening smoking weed there or some owners comes drink beer on the bench. I think like we should maintain this amazing park when our paws friends can have fun together.
Another dusty space. Not a piece of grass, it looks like a prison.
An open space where dogs can run around and meet other dogs

The atmosphere in this park was really tense, as soon as I entered a young woman with a helmet attacked me to tell me that I had to close the door because it's a dog park, plus there were only 2 people in the park, too bad I really just came to rest, it was a failure... I won't come back again
The least developed park in the area. It can be greatly improved by adding plants.
It's not really a park since there is no greenery but only gravel which is dangerous for dog paws!

A small dirt dog park with no vegetation, which is very sad at first glance. Avoid coming if it's raining, come if you're in the area, it can stretch your companion, otherwise go to the Bois de Vincennes!

Rather nice dog park on Sundays, a little small and without green space, but it has the merit of existing. Dogs can move around and have fun without a leash. The dog owners are attentive and welcoming to each other, and keep the place clean.
The town hall does everything to dissuade us from using it. Removal of trash cans, benches stained with uncleaned pigeon droppings
Dog park, convenient for dog owners.

Notice to dog owners who frequent Denfert Park: the Mayor of the 14th is meeting on Wednesday September 13 at 9 a.m. to discuss the future of the Arago Garden which currently refuses access to dogs. We invite all dog owners to come and protest in front of the doors of the Jardin bd Arago from 9 a.m.!

Very good park but quickly saturated given that it is not large and that it is the only sufficiently large central dog park in the 14th, 6th. A water point is missing, the only one of the 3 parks on Place Denfert not to have a fountain
In the evening it is impossible to leave the dog free to play, as many people without dogs sit on the benches doing their own business.
Wonderful for dogs, no water fountain, too bad
This square is very good. Unfortunately it is poorly perceived by outsiders. But when we are there there is a good atmosphere between the masters and dogs

Dog park located in the heart of the 14th arrondissement of Paris. It's a little island of happiness for our 4-legged friends, even if the town hall should agree to make more efforts for basic improvements: double doors, maintenance, waste management as in all parks. This represents a paltry cost compared to the number of people who use this park and the taxes they pay.

The dog space initiative in Paris must be encouraged, we want more! This one is nice. The entrance could be reinforced with a more secure double door to always be sure that our doggies do not run away. But overall good.

Dog park which has the merit of existing and which could be a good alternative to have a good time with your companion, if only irresponsible owners accompanied by dangerous dogs did not allow themselves to come and spoil these moments between properly educated dogs. My beagle was violently bitten on the ear today by a white and black staffy type dog. Her mistress barely reacted and dared to say without apologizing "Ah, she has her heat"... but what kind of master are you to be so lacking in intelligence. Not an exchange, and no reaction from him. I find this unacceptable. I hope that this person will recognize themselves and that they will no longer be welcome.  We are all responsible for our four-legged friends! Let's keep that in mind.
Park dedicated to our dog friends, good idea to let them roam without risk, small space to keep them in sight. You can still stop there even if you don't walk on all fours!
Good idea to create dog parks in Paris. This one is a little small with a sand floor, but the doggies can have fun there without a leash! However, be careful of rat traps...
Tiny, no greenery, just dirt and a gloomy monument in the middle. Long live dog owners in Paris!

We go there every Sunday and this park in Paris is great even if it is small it allows the dogs to play freely. On the other hand, think about going around to check that there is nothing dangerous because I have already found chocolate and grapes in plants.
I only stopped there for a hiking appointment. As far as I could see, this square is only a park for dogs... Despite the cleanliness of the place, the smell is very olfactory.
Sad, muddy and dirty. No bags available. Having a dog in Paris is as encouraged as having a car.
Practical for being able to let the dogs go, but it's a shame to be on the ground without a blade of grass üòû ‚Ä¶
The largest dog park in the south. On the other hand, it is in the ground
Nice caniparc in Denfert-Rochereau, ideal for meeting other friends for our dogs and having fun!
Dog park üê∂ nice to see them having fun in the heart of Paris ‚Ä¶
Nice square for lunch but sometimes poorly attended, not recommended for children.
Nice little park where we can let our 4-legged friends run around
A magnificent site, very relaxing and well maintained, apart from the Wi-Fi which is disconnected by itself...at times
Small park for dogs
One of the few dog parks in Paris. It's not great but it's the only option around.
Ideal place for our four-legged friends to relax...
One of the best dog parks in Paris.
Superb green playground for children in Paris 14
